==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Malar
<hw>Ma"lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>mala</ets> the
cheek: cf. F. <ets>malaire</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or
pertaining to the region of the cheek bone, or to the malar bone;
jugal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>malar</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: malar
<hw>ma"lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The
cheek bone, which forms a part of the lower edge of the orbit; that arch
of bone beneath the eye that forms the prominence of the cheek; also
called the <altname>malar bone</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cheekbone, zygomatic bone, malar bone, jugal bone,
os zygomaticum.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>malar bone</ent>⟦br⟧
